        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-01-28 20:59:58.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nfabric8.io docker-maven-plugin already supports setting system properties using buildArgs. So the predefined proxy settings can be transparently overridden through buildArgs. All that had to be done was to export them as system properties from within the dockerfile and make use of them through the tooling scripts (deploy-artifact specifically) for any maven commandline if supplied. Also, system properties take precedence over the build properties and hence, they are also exposed via base.conf if needed to be changed. Reference: https://dmp.fabric8.io/#build-buildargs.\n\nTested successfully docker build with and without proxy build overrides.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
